**Title: [Authenticated File Upload → Remote Code Execution] in [Pet-Grooming-Management-System] <= [v1.0]**
**BUG Author: Kuldeep Sahu**

**Product Information**

Vendor Homepage: https://www.sourcecodester.com/
Software Link: [https://www.sourcecodester.com/php/xxxx/pet-grooming-management-system.html]
Affected Version: <= v1.0

**Vulnerability Details**

Type: Authenticated File Upload → Remote Code Execution (RCE)
Affected URL: http://localhost/petgrooming_erp/pet_grooming/admin/profile.php
Vulnerable Parameter: File Upload Field (Profile Image)
Vulnerable Files:[admin/profile.php]
Web accessible upload directory http://localhost/petgrooming_erp/pet_grooming/assets/uploadImage/Profile/
Vulnerability Type: CWE-434 (Unrestricted Upload of File with Dangerous Type)
Severity Level: CRITICAL (CVSS: 9.8)

**Root Cause**

The application fails to validate or sanitize uploaded files. Attackers can upload PHP webshells (e.g., shell.php), which are stored in a publicly accessible folder. Direct access to the file allows remote code execution.

**Impact**

Remote Code Execution on server
Full compromise of web application
Possible privilege escalation and lateral movement
Database dump and credential theft
Server takeover

**Proof of Concept (PoC)**
Step1:- Login with valid user credentials.
Step2:- Navigate to Profile Page section → Upload Image
Step3:- Upload a PHP file
